d up just… so bad.</p>", "description_for_label": ["<p>&#8220;I love the Power Glove… it&#8217;s so bad.&#8221; – Lucas (Jackey Vinson) in <i>The Wizard</i>.</p>\n<p>In 1989, &#8216;bad&#8217; was slang for cool and there was nothing cooler than the Power Glove. At least, that&#8217;s what a generation who believed its marketing thought. Developed by Mattel as an alternative controller for the Nintendo Entertainment System (NES), the Power Glove promised to bridge the human-machine divide through early VR mechanics. Just slip on the glove to control your favourite NES games. Except it didn’t really work - well, not in the seamless way the Nintendo-produced movie <i>The Wizard</i> (1989) promised. The Power Glove’s prototype, the DataGlove, did work, but to be affordable for consumers it was simplified and ended up just… so bad.</p>"], "credit_line_for_label": "", "details": [{"label": "Curatorial section", "display_values": ["The Story of the Moving Image&nbsp;→ Moving Pictures&nbsp;→ 08. Immersive Innovations&nbsp;→ MI-08-C01"]}], "stats": {"tap_count": 4649}, "links": [], "creators_primary": [{"id": 1053480, "name": "Mattel", "creator_id": 70587, "role": "creator", "role_id": 968, "is_primary": true}], "creators_other": [], "video_links": [], "media_note": null, "images": [{"id": 12464, "image_file": "https://acmi-public-api.s3.amazonaws.com/image/AEO177791_PowerGlove.jpg", "image_file_thumbnail": "https://acmi-public-api.s3.amazonaws.com/image/AEO177791_PowerGlove.jpg.1200x1200_q85.jpg", "image_file_xs": "https://acmi-public-api.s3.amazonaws.com/image/AEO177791_PowerGlove.jpg.480x480_q85.jpg", "image_file_s": "https://acmi-public-api.s3.amazonaws.com/image/AEO177791_PowerGlove.jpg.960x960_q85.jpg", "image_file_m": "https://acmi-public-api.s3.amazonaws.com/image/AEO177791_PowerGlove.jpg.1920x1920_q85.jpg", "image_file_l": "https://acmi-public-api.s3.amazonaws.com/image/AEO177791_PowerGlove.jpg.3840x3840_q85.jpg", "caption": "AEO177791_PowerGlove", "credit_line": "